{"tid":2195693,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"分析蔡英文亞太安全對話 CNN：台灣決心建立反中聯盟","createTime":"2020-09-09T10:41:12.000Z","updateTime":"2020-09-09T11:23:01.000Z","uid":337052,"like":32,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":14,"replies":[{"pid":"b7600b3987fbcfee5d06cdc5492a680cbb2b901f","tid":2195693,"uid":337052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T10:41:12.000Z","msg":"分析蔡英文亞太安全對話 CNN：台灣決心建立反中聯盟<br />\n   <br />\n2020/09/09 18:09<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://img.ltn.com.tw/Upload/news/600/2020/09/09/phpYyiawe.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimg.ltn.com.tw%2FUpload%2Fnews%2F600%2F2020%2F09%2F09%2FphpYyiawe.jpg&h=efd6bfc5&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n總統蔡英文8日出席「凱達格蘭論壇－2020亞 太安全對話開幕典禮」。 （資料照）<br />\n<br />\n〔即時新聞／綜合報導〕總統蔡英文8日上午出席「凱達格蘭論壇－2020亞太安全對話開幕典禮」，發表演說，<span class=\"red\">美國《有線電視新聞網》（CNN）對此分析，「隨著中國官媒警告可能對美國實施制裁，台灣似乎決心建立反北京聯盟。」</span><br />\n<br />\n蔡英文昨日在「凱達格蘭論壇－2020亞太安全對話開幕典禮」演說指出，「台灣站在捍衛民主，防止集權入侵的最前線」、「印太等區域理念相同的國家和民主友人應討論一個架構，以持續合作維護戰略秩序，嚇阻片面侵略的行為。我們需要一個鼓勵合作、透明的戰略秩序，透過對話而非戰爭威脅來解決問題。我們需要一個既能避戰，又能清楚傳達我們決心捍衛民主的戰略。」<br />\n<br />\n《CNN》分析，蔡英文的演說措辭沒有明確提到中國，但她「指的是誰」無庸置疑，目前為止，沒有任何一個國家對做出的支持比美國還多，而美方舉動並沒有被中國忽視，除了官方發聲抗議外，官媒也警告「繼續與台灣接觸可能會帶來重大後果」，甚至言明「台灣是與中國建立夥伴關係的試金石」，北京似乎也決心要阻止台灣與其他國家建立反對陣線。<br />\n<a href=\"https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/politics/breakingnews/3286652\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fbreakingnews%2F3286652&d=Yvf7L03l0%2FKFASkGPCPwg4RM%2FwdnRWUJBfohchWxIRY%3D&h=ee92f4a1\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fbreakingnews%2F3286652&h=68c52454\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/politics/breakingnews/3286652</a>"},{"pid":"4b4ee80973880a5fa7576ad39588d73fcd14e181","tid":2195693,"uid":337052,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-09T10:42:51.000Z","msg":"Taiwan appears determined to create an anti-Beijing alliance as Chinese state media warns of potential sanctions against US<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nAnalysis by James Griffiths, CNN<br />\n<br />\nUpdated 0652 GMT (1452 HKT) September 9, 2020<br />\n<br />\nHong Kong (CNN)Taiwan's President Tsai Ing-wen wants to create an alliance to defend &quot;freedom, safety, human rights and democracy&quot; in Asia, as the self-ruled island faces renewed pressure from neighboring China.<br />\n<br />\nThough she did not mention China explicitly in her speech, given at a security forum in Taipei, Tsai left little doubt over who she was referring to, saying Taiwan was at the forefront of &quot;defending democracy from authoritarian aggression.&quot;<br />\nTsai's speech came as a Chinese state-backed tabloid reported that foreign officials who visit Taiwan, as well as international companies that do business on the self-ruled island, could face sanctions from Beijing -- the latest potential move by China to rein in Taiwan's growing stature worldwide.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/09/asia/taiwan-china-us-sanctions-intl-hnk/index.html?utm_medium=social&amp;utm_term=image&amp;utm_source=twCNN&amp;utm_content=2020-09-09T08%3A20%3A03\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2020%2F09%2F09%2Fasia%2Ftaiwan-china-us-sanctions-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%3Futm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_term%3Dimage%26utm_source%3DtwCNN%26utm_content%3D2020-09-09T08%253A20%253A03&d=Yvf7L03l0%2FKFASkGPCPwg4RM%2FwdnRWUJBfohchWxIRY%3D&h=047fa1b4\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2020%2F09%2F09%2Fasia%2Ftaiwan-china-us-sanctions-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%3Futm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_term%3Dimage%26utm_source%3DtwCNN%26utm_content%3D2020-09-09T08%253A20%253A03&h=0013e672\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://edition.cnn.com/2020/09/09/asia/taiwan-china-us-sanctions-intl-hnk/index.html?utm_medium=social&amp;utm_term=image&amp;utm_source=twCNN&amp;utm_content=2020-09-09T08%3A20%3A03</a>"},{"pid":"09355e1b4ebf080e200a7b8